criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
1. Patients undergoing simple CABG (on-pump/off-pump) for the first time.
2. Patients who signed the informed consent form and willing to undergo cardiac denervation.
Exclusion Criteria:
1. Age > 75；
2. Emergent CABG;
3. Cardiac surgery history；
4. EF < 40%；
5. Moderate or severer mitral valve regurgitation;
6. Receiving other cardiac surgery except of CABG at the same time；
7. Requiring mechanical or pharmacological therapy for hemodynamic support before CABG, such as ECMO or IABP;
8. History of AF last 6 months;
9. Taking antiarrhythmic agents except of beta-blockers last 2 weeks;
10. Untreated hypothyroidism；
11. Serum creatinine > 150 umol/L.
